{"id":"28f5aced-86a7-4bfd-9a68-ca4eb0697ede","cefr_level":"B1","text_id":"01-b1","text_translated":"NASA is studying asteroids, which are rocks that fly through space. The agency is now working to record data about smaller asteroids that are 140 metres wide or more. Although scientists believe there are about 25,000 asteroids of this size, they have only found about 8,000 so far. This is a serious danger because when a much smaller asteroid exploded over a Russian city in 2013, it injured 1,200 people.","version":2,"created_at":"2025-08-30T18:51:12.345678","updated_at":"2025-08-30T18:51:12.345678"}
```

