{"id":"7c415f1c-a301-4d6e-81ec-cc7983e555e8","cefr_level":"B1","text_id":"text_001","text_translated":"NASA is now working to log smaller asteroids, which are rocks that fly through space, focusing on those that measure 140 metres wide or more. Although scientists estimate there are 25,000 asteroids of this size, only about 8,000 have been found so far, which means 17,000 are still unaccounted for. These middle-sized asteroids would be a serious danger if they entered Earth's orbit, especially because a much smaller asteroid injured 1,200 people when it exploded above a Russian city in 2013.","version":16,"created_at":"2025-08-30T18:58:39.614810","updated_at":"2025-08-30T18:59:53.241139"}
```
